cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.ET

The paper presents a new training algorithm for spiking neural networks, which is a subfield of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The algorithm is based on back propagation with binary activations, which is a technique used in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also applies the algorithm to image classification tasks (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the hardware implementation of the algorithm, which falls under the category of electronic and computer engineering (cs.ET).
